Step 1: Recognize that the given vectors $\overrightarrow{AB}$, $\overrightarrow{AC}$, and $\overrightarrow{BC}$ are all perpendicular to each other.

Step 2: Recall that the dot product of two perpendicular vectors equals the product of their magnitudes.

Step 3: Calculate the magnitudes of $\overrightarrow{AB}$, $\overrightarrow{AC}$, and $\overrightarrow{BC}$.

\begin{align*}
|\overrightarrow{AB}| &= a, \\
|\overrightarrow{AC}| &= a, \\
|\overrightarrow{BC}| &= a.
\end{align*}

Step 4: Calculate the dot product $\overrightarrow{AB} \cdot \overrightarrow{AC}$.

\begin{align*}
\overrightarrow{AB} \cdot \overrightarrow{AC} &= a \cdot a \cdot \cos 60^\circ \\
&= a^2 \cdot \frac{1}{2} \\
&= \frac{a^2}{2}.
\end{align*}

Step 5: Calculate the dot product $\overrightarrow{AC} \cdot \overrightarrow{BC}$.

\begin{align*}
\overrightarrow{AC} \cdot \overrightarrow{BC} &= a \cdot a \cdot \cos 120^\circ \\
&= a^2 \cdot \frac{1}{2} \\
&= \frac{a^2}{2}.
\end{align*}

Step 6: Add the results of the dot products together.

\begin{align*}
\overrightarrow{AB} \cdot \overrightarrow{AC} + \overrightarrow{AC} \cdot \overrightarrow{BC} &= \frac{a^2}{2} + \frac{a^2}{2} \\
&= a^2.
\end{align*}

Final answer: $\boxed{a^2}$

problem:
Jia and Yi are solving the system of equations simultaneously:
$$
\begin{cases}
& ax+by=2, \\
& cx-3y=-2.
\end{cases}
$$
Jia correctly solves to get
$$
\begin{cases}
& x=1, \\
& y=-1;
\end{cases}
$$
Yi, due to copying the value of $c$ incorrectly, gets the wrong solution
$$
\begin{cases}
& x=2, \\
& y=-6.
\end{cases}
$$
Find the values of $a$, $b$, and $c$.
